        "body": "## 🚀 Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR implements the core functionality of the YouTube clone by connecting the frontend to the mock backend and building the main user-facing pages and reusable components.\r\n\r\n## ✅ Features Implemented\r\n\r\n### 📡 API Integration\r\n\r\n* Integrated `axios` with local `json-server`\r\n* Created reusable `useFetch` hook\r\n* Added loading and error handling states\r\n\r\n### 🏠 Pages Completed\r\n\r\n* **Home Page**\r\n\r\n  * Displays all videos from backend\r\n  * Category-based filtering support\r\n* **Watch Page**\r\n\r\n  * Video playback with metadata (views, likes, upload time)\r\n  * Integrated `likedVideos` and `watchHistory`\r\n  * Displays related videos\r\n  * Includes comment section\r\n* **Search Page**\r\n\r\n  * Query-based filtering (`/search?q=...`)\r\n  * Handles empty results state\r\n* **Channel Page**\r\n\r\n  * Channel details and video listing\r\n\r\n### 🧩 Components Built\r\n\r\n* `VideoCard` – reusable video preview card\r\n* `VideoPlayer` – responsive video player\r\n* `CommentSection` – structured comments UI\r\n* `ChannelHeader` – channel info layout\r\n* `CategoryFilter` – category selection UI\r\n\r\n### 🔀 Routing\r\n\r\n* Replaced placeholder routes with actual pages:\r\n\r\n  * `/` → Home\r\n  * `/watch/:id`\r\n  * `/search`\r\n  * `/channel/:id`\r\n  * `/liked`\r\n  * `/history`\r\n\r\n## 🔗 State Management\r\n\r\n* Integrated existing `AppContext`:\r\n\r\n  * `likedVideos`\r\n  * `watchHistory`\r\n* Ensured persistence via `localStorage`\r\n\r\n## 🎯 Outcome\r\n\r\n* Core app flow is now functional\r\n* Videos load dynamically from backend\r\n* Navigation between pages works correctly\r\n* Ready for final polish, testing, and deployment\r\n\r\n## 📝 Notes\r\n\r\n* No breaking changes\r\n* Styling improvements kept minimal and functional\r\n* Remaining work includes:\r\n\r\n  * README\r\n  * testing\r\n  * deployment setup\r\n",
